INSERT INTO `knowledge_article` VALUES (1,1,1,'Audio/Video Device Not Working','2018-05-18','<ul>\r\n<li>Are you having trouble hearing your student or vice versa?</li>\r\n<li>Is your video not showing during lesson?<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>You need to conduct AC device checking.</strong><br /><br />&rArr;Highly recommended: Conduct device checking before your lesson starts.</p>\r\n<p>Follow these steps on how to:</p>\r\n<p>1. Device check window always pop out first after log in but it can also be access by clicking&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/detection.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"38\" />on AC main window.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/device check.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"568\" height=\"369\" /></p>\r\n<p>2. Click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/startDetect.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"122\" height=\"43\" /></p>\r\n<p>3. Follow the instructions on the interactive video</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/interactive.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"566\" height=\"342\" /></p>\r\n<p>4. Test your speaker and choose an option (whether Yes or No)</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/test-speaker.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"338\" /></p>\r\n<p>5. Test your microphone.</p>\r\n<p><em>- moving red bars indicate that your microphone is working</em></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/test-mic.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"338\" /></p>\r\n<p>6. Test your camera.</p>\r\n<p><em>- you should be able to see yourself</em></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/test-cam.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"558\" height=\"337\" /></p>\r\n<p>7. The result of the checking will be summarized at the end</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/deviceCheckResult.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"555\" height=\"335\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2017-06-05 00:22:33','2018-05-22 02:52:14'),(2,1,1,'Install AC','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Download the latest version of AC &ndash; go to your MyPage account click on the AC icon on your booking schedule</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-110\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1341px) 100vw, 1341px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13.jpg 1341w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13-300x104.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13-768x267.jpg 768w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13-1024x357.jpg 1024w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/13-1200x418.jpg 1200w\" alt=\"13\" width=\"1341\" height=\"467\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>*You may also contact Technical Helpdesk for the link.</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2.&nbsp;Locate AC Installer on your Downloads folder and double-click to run.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-111\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/14.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/14.jpg 663w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/14-300x219.jpg 300w\" alt=\"14\" width=\"663\" height=\"484\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3.&nbsp;Click Run if you are prompted with a security warning window.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-112\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/15.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 414px) 100vw, 414px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/15.jpg 414w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/15-300x225.jpg 300w\" alt=\"15\" width=\"414\" height=\"310\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4. On the installer window, choose and click English as the language.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-113\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/17.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/17.jpg 612w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/17-300x222.jpg 300w\" alt=\"17\" width=\"612\" height=\"452\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5.&nbsp;Place a check mark to agree to the License Agreement then click&nbsp;<strong>Quick Installation</strong> button.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-114\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/18.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/18.jpg 612w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/18-300x222.jpg 300w\" alt=\"18\" width=\"612\" height=\"452\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">6.&nbsp;Wait for the whole installation process to finish.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-115\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/19.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/19.jpg 612w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/19-300x222.jpg 300w\" alt=\"19\" width=\"612\" height=\"452\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">7.&nbsp;After installing, AC log in window will open &ndash; enter your username and password to log in.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-116\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/20.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 268px) 100vw, 268px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/20.jpg 268w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/20-221x300.jpg 221w\" alt=\"20\" width=\"268\" height=\"364\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the TECH chat bubble at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:25:27','2017-06-05 00:26:20'),(3,1,1,'Uninstall AC','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1.&nbsp;Make sure that your current AC is properly closed and not running.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2.&nbsp;Open Control Panel</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2 ways:</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Press and hold the windows key&nbsp;<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-86\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/windows.jpg\" alt=\"windows\" width=\"29\" height=\"29\" />&nbsp;then type R to open the Run window.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Type&nbsp;<strong><em>appwiz.cpl&nbsp;</em></strong>click OK</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-94\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/12.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 413px) 100vw, 413px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/12.jpg 413w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/12-300x154.jpg 300w\" alt=\"12\" width=\"413\" height=\"212\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click start&nbsp;<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-87\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/start.jpg\" alt=\"start\" width=\"34\" height=\"25\" />&nbsp;on your PC then select Control Panel</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-99\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/16.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 413px) 100vw, 413px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/16.jpg 413w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/16-195x300.jpg 195w\" alt=\"16\" width=\"413\" height=\"635\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3. On the Control Panel window, click Uninstall a program.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-88\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/06.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 628px) 100vw, 628px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/06.jpg 853w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/06-300x211.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/06-768x540.jpg 768w\" alt=\"06\" width=\"628\" height=\"442\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4.&nbsp;On the Programs and Features window, locate and select AC.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-90\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/07.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 591px) 100vw, 591px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/07.jpg 591w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/07-300x213.jpg 300w\" alt=\"07\" width=\"591\" height=\"420\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5.&nbsp;Right-click on AC then click Uninstall/Change</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/08.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 589px) 100vw, 589px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/08.jpg 589w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/08-300x211.jpg 300w\" alt=\"08\" width=\"589\" height=\"414\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">6. On the AC uninstaller package,&nbsp;Click&nbsp;<strong>Proceed to uninstall</strong> button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-91\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/09.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 380px) 100vw, 380px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/09.jpg 380w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/09-300x223.jpg 300w\" alt=\"09\" width=\"380\" height=\"283\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">7.&nbsp;Wait for the process to finish</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-92\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/10.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 379px) 100vw, 379px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/10.jpg 379w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/10-300x215.jpg 300w\" alt=\"10\" width=\"379\" height=\"272\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">8.&nbsp;Once un-installation is done, it should prompt you that uninstall is complete.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-93\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/11.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/11.jpg 532w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/11-300x222.jpg 300w\" alt=\"11\" width=\"532\" height=\"393\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the TECH chat bubble at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:26:12','2017-06-05 00:26:12'),(4,1,1,'Restarting AC Manually after Encountering Issues','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1.) Download &ldquo;kill AC Task&rdquo; file <span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><a style=\"color: #3366ff;\" href=\"http://tinyurl.com/kill-AC-task\">here</a></span>.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The file looks like this:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img src=\"http://support.51talk.com/scripts/file.php?view=Y&amp;file=187a146c9d1e899e65ed095d9db976ce\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2.) After downloading, right click on the &ldquo;kill AC Task&rdquo; file and choose &ldquo;run as admin&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img src=\"http://support.51talk.com/scripts/file.php?view=Y&amp;file=191fcd0bf76b38c3d16a5d44b77625f0\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3.) Once you run the file, you will see this black screen. Then just press any key.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4.) After pressing any key the black screen will close.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img style=\"width: 507px;\" src=\"http://support.51talk.com/scripts/file.php?view=Y&amp;file=2bc3e5b9f84bb0ee1b9a945cd765521a\" height=\"256\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5.) You may now Open AC and log in again.</span></p>','2017-06-05 00:27:19','2018-05-22 02:58:33'),(6,1,2,'Install and Log-in to AC','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Installation:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Launch appstore and search 51Talk AC then click to open page.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-316\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/92.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 781px) 100vw, 781px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/92.jpg 781w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/92-300x197.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/92-768x503.jpg 768w\" alt=\"92\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Click Get button to install.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-317\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/93.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/93.jpg 780w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/93-300x197.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/93-768x505.jpg 768w\" alt=\"93\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3. Wait for the installation process to finish</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-318\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/94.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 784px) 100vw, 784px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/94.jpg 784w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/94-300x197.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/94-768x504.jpg 768w\" alt=\"94\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Log-in:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Launch AC from applications folder then enter your login details</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-319\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/95.jpg\" alt=\"95\" width=\"203\" height=\"259\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. You will be directed to AC main menu where you will view all booked lessons</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>*To enter the classroom, click the <strong>Enter</strong> button</em></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-321\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/97.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 624px) 100vw, 624px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/97.jpg 624w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/97-300x271.jpg 300w\" alt=\"97\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-324\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/100.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 997px) 100vw, 997px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/100.jpg 997w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/100-300x186.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/100-768x476.jpg 768w\" alt=\"100\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3. To log out, click on 51talk AC on the menu bar then select Quit 51talk AC or press command key (<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-322\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/99.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 15px) 100vw, 15px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/99.jpg 168w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/99-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"99\" width=\"15\" height=\"16\" />)&nbsp;+ Q on your keyboard.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-323\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/98.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 790px) 100vw, 790px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/98.jpg 790w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/98-300x229.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/98-768x587.jpg 768w\" alt=\"98\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the TECH chat bubble at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:30:00','2017-08-02 05:28:08'),(12,4,0,'Appearance Checker – Choose default camera','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Too many webcams installed in your PC?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Set the webcam that you use on your appearance checker. Just follow these steps on how-to:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Open camera settings</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click on the camera icon on the appearance checker then select <strong>Settings<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-225\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/52.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 546px) 100vw, 546px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/52.jpg 546w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/52-300x188.jpg 300w\" alt=\"52\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Adobe Flash Player Settings window</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the camera icon</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-226\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/53.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 422px) 100vw, 422px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/53.jpg 422w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/53-300x209.jpg 300w\" alt=\"53\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Choose the camera that you want to use on the drop down list.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/54.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 432px) 100vw, 432px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/54.jpg 432w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/54-300x212.jpg 300w\" alt=\"54\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Check if camera is working</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click on the camera thumbnail to check if your camera is working.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/55.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 577px) 100vw, 577px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/55.jpg 577w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/55-300x177.jpg 300w\" alt=\"55\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*If prompted, allow the website to access your camera by clicking Allow</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-229\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/56.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 364px) 100vw, 364px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/56.jpg 364w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/56-300x114.jpg 300w\" alt=\"56\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*You should be able to see yourself on the thumbnail.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-230\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/57.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 276px) 100vw, 276px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/57.jpg 276w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/57-231x300.jpg 231w\" alt=\"57\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click close then proceed with the appearance checker.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Refer to this article on how-to: MyPage Appearance Checker</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:42:05','2017-08-02 05:34:04'),(13,4,0,'My Booking Schedule Alignment Error','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Is your booking scheduled not aligned?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Adjust your browser&rsquo;s resolution.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;My booking schedule not aligned<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-264\" style=\"width: 456px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/67.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 685px) 100vw, 685px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/67.jpg 685w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/67-300x235.jpg 300w\" alt=\"67\" height=\"358\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Browser resolution may not be set to default (100%)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Adjust browser screen resolution</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Set browser resolution to default (100%)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Google Chrome</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the magnifying glass then click Set to Default button.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-265\" style=\"width: 434px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/68.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/68.jpg 657w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/68-300x103.jpg 300w\" alt=\"68\" height=\"149\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Mozilla Firefox</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Open browser menu then adjust resolution to 100%</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-267\" style=\"width: 433px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/70.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 549px) 100vw, 549px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/70.jpg 549w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/70-300x125.jpg 300w\" alt=\"70\" height=\"180\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2017-06-05 00:42:46','2018-05-18 03:01:51'),(14,4,0,'MyPage Appearance Checker','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Having trouble going through the Appearance Checker in MyPage?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Log-in to MyPage &ndash; <span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><a style=\"color: #3366ff;\" href=\"http://www.51talk.com/ph\">www.51talk.com/ph</a></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Click the <u>check appearance now</u> button.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-251\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/61.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/61.jpg 560w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/61-300x191.jpg 300w\" alt=\"61\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Allow MyPage to access your camera.<br />*Click the <u>Allow</u> button<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-252\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/62.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/62.jpg 562w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/62-300x86.jpg 300w\" alt=\"62\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>4.&nbsp;Position yourself in front of your camera then click the capture button<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-253\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/63.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 382px) 100vw, 382px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/63.jpg 382w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/63-300x268.jpg 300w\" alt=\"63\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">**Make sure to follow the proper guidelines:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-254\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/64.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/64.jpg 399w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/64-271x300.jpg 271w\" alt=\"64\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>5.&nbsp;You should be prompted by a window that the image has been saved successfully. Then click the <u>OK&nbsp;</u>button.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-255\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/65.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 545px) 100vw, 545px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/65.jpg 545w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/65-300x77.jpg 300w\" alt=\"65\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>6.&nbsp;Click the <u>Enter my page</u> button to enter your account.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-256\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/66.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/66.jpg 560w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/66-300x201.jpg 300w\" alt=\"66\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>**Once you successfully upload/capture a photo but were still prompted to capture a photo, you may just click on Enter MyPage button (as long as you have successfully captured a photo).</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:59:56','2017-08-02 05:35:34'),(15,5,0,'Clear Cache and Cookies','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Open browser history settings &ndash; Google Chrome</strong>&nbsp;<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-165\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/chrome.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 30px) 100vw, 30px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/chrome.jpg 195w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/chrome-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"chrome\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Customize and control Google Chrome button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-166\" style=\"width: 410px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/35.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/35.jpg 428w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/35-300x86.jpg 300w\" alt=\"35\" height=\"118\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Open History page</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-167\" style=\"width: 437px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/36.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/36.jpg 532w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/36-300x205.jpg 300w\" alt=\"36\" height=\"299\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Clear browsing data button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-168\" style=\"width: 457px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37.jpg 889w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37-300x118.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37-768x302.jpg 768w\" alt=\"37\" height=\"180\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Place a check mark on all options. Choose &ldquo;the beginning of time&rdquo; on the drop down then click Clear browsing data button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169\" style=\"width: 460px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/38.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 504px) 100vw, 504px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/38.jpg 504w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/38-300x259.jpg 300w\" alt=\"38\" height=\"397\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Wait for the whole process to finish then reload your browser.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Open browser history settings &ndash; Mozilla Firefox&nbsp;<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-170\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/firefox.jpg\" alt=\"firefox\" width=\"28\" height=\"26\" /></strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Open menu button then click History</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-171\" style=\"width: 362px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/39.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/39.jpg 421w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/39-250x300.jpg 250w\" alt=\"39\" height=\"435\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Clear Recent History</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-172\" style=\"width: 265px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/40.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 285px) 100vw, 285px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/40.jpg 285w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/40-152x300.jpg 152w\" alt=\"40\" height=\"524\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Select &ldquo;Everything&rdquo; on the drop down. Place a check mark on the highlighted list then click Clear Now button.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-173\" style=\"width: 300px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/41.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 361px) 100vw, 361px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/41.jpg 361w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/41-300x293.jpg 300w\" alt=\"41\" height=\"293\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Wait for the whole process to finish then reload your browser.</span></p>','2017-06-05 01:01:17','2018-05-18 02:57:29'),(16,5,0,'Disabling Other Webcam Installed','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;View installed webcam</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click start/windows button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Type Device Manager on the Search box then click Device Manager</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-187\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/42.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 336px) 100vw, 336px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/42.jpg 336w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/42-195x300.jpg 195w\" alt=\"42\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Disable other installed camera device</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the arrow on Imaging devices</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click on the camera device that you don&rsquo;t use then click Disable</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:</strong> The camera that you are currently using should be listed on the Imaging device. If not, re-plug or install your camera&rsquo;s driver.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-188\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/44.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/44.jpg 555w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/44-300x178.jpg 300w\" alt=\"44\" /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:01:53','2017-08-02 05:36:57'),(17,5,0,'How to Install Flash Player Active X','2017-06-05','<p><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">For Windows OS</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Use <strong>Internet Explorer</strong> browser to open Adobe Flash Website.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Link:&nbsp;http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Click&nbsp;on &ldquo;Need Flash Player for a different computer?&rdquo; link.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-338\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1002px) 100vw, 1002px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101.jpg 1002w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101-300x181.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101-768x462.jpg 768w\" alt=\"101\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3.&nbsp;For &ldquo;Step 1&rdquo; select the Operating System that corresponds to your computer&rsquo;s Operating System (ex. Windows 7)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-340\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1004px) 100vw, 1004px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103.jpg 1004w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103-768x420.jpg 768w\" alt=\"103\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4.&nbsp;For &ldquo;Step 2&rdquo; select &ldquo;FP for Internet Explorer &ndash; Active X&rdquo;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-341\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1005px) 100vw, 1005px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104.jpg 1005w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104-768x420.jpg 768w\" alt=\"104\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5. Uncheck all box under Optional Offers</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-342\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1005px) 100vw, 1005px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105.jpg 1005w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105-768x420.jpg 768w\" alt=\"105\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">6. Click the <strong>Download now</strong> button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-343\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1006px) 100vw, 1006px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106.jpg 1006w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106-768x419.jpg 768w\" alt=\"106\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">7. Wait for the process to finish</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-348\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/107.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/107.jpg 713w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/107-300x181.jpg 300w\" alt=\"107\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">8.&nbsp;If this yellow bar appear below, just click on &ldquo;Save&rdquo;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-349\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/108.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/108.jpg 713w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/108-300x199.jpg 300w\" alt=\"108\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">9.&nbsp;Once download is complete you will see the white bar below then just click &ldquo;Open Folder&rdquo; to see the installer that you have downloaded.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-350\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/109.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 718px) 100vw, 718px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/109.jpg 718w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/109-300x201.jpg 300w\" alt=\"109\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">10. Open the file to install</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/110.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 716px) 100vw, 716px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/110.jpg 716w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/110-300x113.jpg 300w\" alt=\"110\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">11.&nbsp;If there is a prompt that asks if you want to install updates for adobe flash, just select &ldquo;Allow updates&hellip;.(Recommended) then click &ldquo;Next&rdquo;.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>*Wait for the process to finish<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-352\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 787px) 100vw, 787px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111.jpg 787w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111-300x184.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111-768x471.jpg 768w\" alt=\"111\" /><br /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:03:24','2017-08-02 05:39:42'),(18,5,0,'Set your headset as your default device','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Having audio issues on your teaching apps?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Try to set your headset as the default device of your PC.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;View installed devices.</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click the volume icon on your taskbar (usually beside the time/date of your PC)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Playback devices</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" style=\"width: 372px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/51.jpg\" alt=\"51\" height=\"251\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Set your headset as default Playback Device (Audio)</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click on your headset then click Set as Default Device</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>Note:</em></strong><em> Also set your headset as the Default Communication Device.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-235\" style=\"width: 417px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/58.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 563px) 100vw, 563px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/58.jpg 563w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/58-300x251.jpg 300w\" alt=\"58\" height=\"349\" /><br />*<strong>Note:</strong> After setting your headset as the default device, there should be a green indicator with a check mark on your headset.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236\" style=\"width: 236px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/59.jpg\" alt=\"59\" height=\"81\" /><br /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Set your headset as default Recording Device (Microphone)</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Go to Recording tab on the Sounds window. Right-click on your headset and click Set as Default Device.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>Note:</em></strong><em> Also set your headset as the Default Communication Device.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-237\" style=\"width: 395px;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/60.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/60.jpg 599w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/60-300x232.jpg 300w\" alt=\"60\" height=\"305\" /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>*Click Apply (if possible) then Click OK</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:05:00','2018-05-18 03:00:29'),(19,5,0,'Setting proxy on your browser','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Workaround to access MyPage using Google Chrome</span><br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>Disclaimer</strong><strong>:</strong> Once the proxy was set, you can only access the 51talk website. Other websites will be inaccessible. If you will access other websites. You may just simply uncheck the check box for proxy server.</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Open your browser</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the <strong>Customize and control Google Chrome</strong> button.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click settings</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1008px) 100vw, 1008px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1.jpg 1008w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1-300x148.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1-768x378.jpg 768w\" alt=\"45\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;On the search bar, type &ldquo;proxy&rdquo;<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1001px) 100vw, 1001px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1.jpg 1001w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1-300x187.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1-768x480.jpg 768w\" alt=\"46\" /><br /></strong>*Then click the Change proxy settings button.<strong><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Click the LAN Settings button.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/47.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 363px) 100vw, 363px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/47.jpg 363w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/47-236x300.jpg 236w\" alt=\"47\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>4.&nbsp;Local Area Network (LAN) Settings</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Check <strong>Automatically detect settings </strong>under Automatic configuration.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Check the following under Proxy server:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&ndash;&nbsp;Use a proxy server for your LAN (These settings will not apply to dial-up or VPN connections).</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&ndash; Bypass proxy server for local addressess</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Then enter the following details under Proxy server:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Address:</strong> 116.213.69.32</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Port:</strong> 80</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/48.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 405px) 100vw, 405px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/48.jpg 405w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/48-300x262.jpg 300w\" alt=\"48\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>5.&nbsp;Disabling Proxy settings</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Un-check <strong>Use a proxy server for your LAN&hellip;..</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/49.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/49.jpg 402w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/49-300x263.jpg 300w\" alt=\"49\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:06:42','2017-08-02 05:41:22'),(20,6,0,'Network Troubleshooting Basics: Some Simple Steps','2017-06-05','<div class=\"post-meta\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"small\">by</span> <span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"fn\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" title=\"Posts by Ryan D. Lang\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/author/ryandla/\" rel=\"author\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">Ryan D. Lang</a></span></span> <span class=\"small\">on</span><span class=\"post-date updated\"> <abbr class=\"date time published\" title=\"2011-05-30T12:38:13+0200\">May 30, 2011</abbr> </span><span class=\"small\">in</span> <span class=\"categories\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/category/networks/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">Network</a></span> &ndash; Last Update:<span class=\"post_date date updated\"><abbr title=\"2015-01-29T19:23:24+0200\">January 29, 2015</abbr></span><span class=\"post-comments comments\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/30/network-troubleshooting-basics-some-simple-steps/#comments\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">&nbsp;</a></span></span></div>\r\n<div class=\"post-meta\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<section class=\"entry\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This article is the fourth and final part of a series on the basics of network troubleshooting. The tools covered in the previous articles (<a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/12/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ping-command/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">ping</a>, <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/17/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ipconfig-command/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">ipconfig</a>, <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/24/network-troubleshooting-basics-tracert-pathping/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">tracert and pathping</a>) will be combined into a troubleshooting method. This guide will teach you valuable steps in finding where a problem is on a network connection.</span>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Knowing these commands before having to deal with the frustration of a network connection problem is not a bad idea. A working connection shows you what is supposed to happen. If you see something different, you will know something is up. When problems strike, at the least you can get an idea of what is going on.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 0: Check the Cords &amp; Power</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The first thing you should always do is check to make sure everything is plugged in: your computer, router, device, etc. Many laptops have a button to turn off the wireless connection; the icon looks like a signal tower. When in doubt, read the manual (which you can often download from the manufacturer&rsquo;s website). Bear in mind, we all forget this step at some point, so do not feel too silly when it happens to you.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 1: Ping Yourself</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You want to test that your machine is working properly. To do this, you want to ping yourself. You use the loop-back address (127.0.0.1) to do this. Pinging the loop-back address tests to make sure software on your computer is working properly. Typically, if something is not working at this stage, you may just need to restart your computer.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ping</span></p>\r\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"&ldquo;Network Troubleshooting Basics: The Ping Command&rdquo; &mdash; gHacks Technology News\" src=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/12/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ping-command/embed/#?secret=9pypesYRT2\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" data-secret=\"9pypesYRT2\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 2: Ping Your Router (AKA: the Default Gateway)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The next step would be to ping your router. You can find your router&rsquo;s IP address with ipconfig as well (it should be on the bottom of the unit and listed in the manual too). Remember that <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/17/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ipconfig-command/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">ipconfig</a> lists your router as the &ldquo;Default Gateway.&rdquo; It is very likely to be <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/04/29/why-your-home-router-is-192-168-1-1/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">192.168.1.1</a> or a similar number.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This is done to test if your router is responding. If it is not, and you have already checked to make sure it is on, then it may need to be turned off and turned on. Every once in a while it may need a refresh. If the problem continues, contact you ISP for assistance to see if they can help.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Note: Routers, like anything else in the IT world, will someday fail. There is a chance that this has happened. Your ISP help desk should be able to help you determine this. If the router is one of theirs, they will likely send you out a new one.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 3: Ping Yourself with Your IP Address</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">We want to test to make sure everything is working correctly between your router and your computer. To do this, ping your IP address. It is listed in the ipconfig command at the same time the router IP number is. If this works, you can be pretty confident that a problem is outside your home (or maybe small office) network.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 4: Ping and Tracert Outside Your Network</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-109540     lazyloaded\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px\" srcset=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg 677w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-660x404.jpg 660w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-100x61.jpg 100w\" alt=\"network trace\" data-lazy-src=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg\" data-lazy-srcset=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg 677w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-660x404.jpg 660w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-100x61.jpg 100w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px\" /></a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From here, you want to test something outside your network. In a medium or larger network setting, a server on another branch of the network will do. For a home network, the Internet is often your only option. Since chances are the problem is that one or more websites are (or seem) down, this is a logical thing to check.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You can use a few different tools. First try the ping command because it is the fastest. It will only tell you if the site is working or not. For more detailed information, use tracert and pathping. They can give a better idea of what is going on. For instance, if you can reach your router, but no further, the node that connects you to the Internet may be down: an ISP issue. If you can reach only a couple (one or two) steps past your router, then it still is probably an ISP issue. Your Internet is down. If you can reach a lot further, the site may be having issues (see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/02/17/is-facebook-down-find-out-right-now/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">is Facebook down</a>, ways to <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2008/03/16/ways-to-check-if-a-website-is-really-down/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">check if a website is really down</a>, for pointers) There even is a chance that other sites, either from the same proximity or even hosting service, are having the same problem. If it is an e-commerce site, there may be a number to call, but there probably is not much to do besides wait. At least you know where the problem is.</span></p>\r\n</section>','2017-06-05 01:10:32','2017-08-02 05:47:16'),(22,8,0,'How do I install Adobe Acrobat DC for Windows?','2017-06-05','<div class=\"page-description\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow the instructions below to download and install Adobe Acrobat Reader DC on Windows.</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_5\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Mac users</strong>: If you&rsquo;re running Mac OS, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-mac-os.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install Adobe Acrobat Reader DC on Mac OS</a>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"main_System_requirements\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">System requirements</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Before you install, always make sure that your system meets the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/reader/system-requirements.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">minimum system requirements</a>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_1236799004\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h3 id=\"InstallingReaderonolderoperatingsystems\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">INSTALLING READER ON OLDER OPERATING SYSTEMS</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_1060360623\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If your operating system is older,</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">you can install an earlier version of Reader. For step-by-step instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If you&rsquo;re not sure which version of Windows you have, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/which-operating-system\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Which Windows operating system am I running?</a></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"main_Internet_Explorer__Download_and_install_Adobe_Reader\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Explorer: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_1\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Internet Explorer.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step/step_par/image_692742472.img.jpg/get_adobe_reader_dc_windows.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the file download message appears at the bottom of the browser window, click <strong>Run</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Run\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step_2/step_par/img_0.img.png/security_warning.png\" alt=\"Click Run\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click <strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step_4/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_1\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"main_Mozilla_Firefox__Download_and_install_Adobe_Reader\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Firefox: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_2\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Mozilla Firefox.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_458073859/step_par/image_1918909578.img.jpg/win10.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_458073859/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the Opening dialog box appears, click <strong>Save File</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Save File\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_2/step_par/img_0.img.png/save_file_dialog.png\" alt=\"Click Save File\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Press <strong>Ctrl+J</strong> to open the download Library. When the download Library window appears, double-click the .exe file for Reader.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Open the download Library\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_3/step_par/img_0.img.png/download_library1.png\" alt=\"Open the download Library\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If prompted to open the executable file, click <strong>OK</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click OK\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_6/step_par/image_0.img.png/warning_message.png\" alt=\"Click OK\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click&nbsp;<strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_3\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"id_43756\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Chrome: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_4\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Google Chrome.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step/step_par/image_1001882723.img.jpg/win10.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Click <strong>Save</strong> to download the Reader installer.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the downloaded file appears at the bottom of the browser window, click the .exe file for Reader.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click the Reader.exe file at the bottom of the browser\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step_3/step_par/image.img.png/file_saved.png\" alt=\"Click the Reader.exe file at the bottom of the browser\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click&nbsp;<strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step_5/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','2017-06-05 02:04:32','2017-08-02 05:51:47'),(24,1,1,'How to fix common issues after an AC upgrade?','2018-06-19','<ul>\r\n<li>AC Crashing</li>\r\n<li>Courselist Not Loading</li>\r\n<li>Audio/Video Device not Detected</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The things that you can do when you encounter this issues are:</span></em></p>\r\n<p>A. Clean installation of the latest AC version.</p>\r\n<p>B. Clear your AC cache</p>\r\n<p>C. Conduct device checking</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Follow these instructions on how to:</em></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>A. Clean installation of the latest AC version</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>*Uninstall all previous AC version</em><br />1. Go to Control Panel and click on programs (via Start&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/shares/start.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"45\" height=\"33\" />&nbsp;or Windows search bar)</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/shares/Programs.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"183\" height=\"69\" /></p>\r\n<p>2. Select 51Talk AC then click Uninstall/Change</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/shares/ProgramFiles.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"635\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p>3.On the 51Talk AC Uninstaller window, click on <strong>&ldquo;Proceed Uninstall&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/photos/9/Uninstaller.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"615\" height=\"454\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>4.Wait for the uninstallation process to finish.</p>\r\n<p>5.Once uninstallation is complete, you may now start re-installing AC.</p>\r\n<p>6.For the latest version of AC, you may download the latest AC thru your mypage by clicking on this icon:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/shares/Icon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"86\" height=\"83\" /></p>\r\n<p>OR</p>\r\n<p>click on this link: <a href=\"https://ac.51talk.com/PcAc/version/51Talk-AC.2.14.0.54.exe\">https://ac.51talk.com/PcAc/version/51Talk-AC.2.14.0.55.exe</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>B.&nbsp;Clear AC Cache</strong></p>\r\n<p>Clearing AC cache can fix the lesson list or material load failed or display error issue</p>\r\n<p>1.On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/menu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"93\" height=\"40\" /></p>\r\n<p>2.Click on&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/system setting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"127\" height=\"37\" /></p>\r\n<p>3.Click on <strong>Clean Button</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/photos/9/clean.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"375\" height=\"324\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>4.Then click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/yes button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"127\" height=\"36\" /></p>\r\n<p>5.AC will now initialize reboot to take effect</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/complete.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"144\" height=\"62\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>C.&nbsp;Setup Audio and Video Devices</strong></p>\r\n<p>After AC upgrade always redo the test to ensure default devices (Audio / Video) will be selected as default</p>\r\n<p>1.On the <strong>Device Checking </strong>window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/start_detect.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"110\" height=\"38\" /></p>\r\n<p>2.Selecting audio devices &gt; Click on yes if you can hear the instruction guide through your headset as default</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/testSpeaker.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"220\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**Otherwise click NO button and AC will select other Audio device as default.</p>\r\n<p>3.Selecting Microphone &gt; Please try to speak once initiated and an audio bar will be visible if microphone is working, then click yes</p>\r\n<p>4.Otherwise click &ldquo;Dissatisfied&rdquo; button and AC will select other Mic device as default.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/testMic.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"250\" /></p>\r\n<p>5.Selecting video camera &gt; AC will automatically look for Camera devices as default, if ever we wanted to change camera device just click &ldquo;Dissatisfied&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/TestCamera.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"237\" height=\"313\" /></p>','2018-05-18 01:40:41','2018-06-26 01:02:33'),(25,1,1,'What to do when lesson material is not loading','2018-06-19','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3 Steps that you can do in resolving this isssue</p>\r\n<p><strong>A. Refresh your AC</strong></p>\r\n<p>- On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/refresh.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"83\" height=\"32\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>B. Use backup classroom</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>-&nbsp;</strong>On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/backupClassroom.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"148\" height=\"33\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/getLesson.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"361\" height=\"225\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>*Take note that your lesson will only show on your backup classroom within 1 hour of your current time.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>C. Clear your AC\'s cache</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>*It can fix any lesson material loading failed or display error issue</em></span></p>\r\n<p>1.On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/menu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"84\" height=\"36\" /></p>\r\n<p>2.Click on&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/system setting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"113\" height=\"33\" /></p>\r\n<p>3.Click on <strong>Clean Button</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/photos/9/clean.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"396\" height=\"342\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>4.Then click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/yes button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"124\" height=\"35\" /></p>\r\n<p>5.AC will now initialize reboot to take effect</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/complete.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"170\" height=\"73\" /></p>','2018-05-18 01:49:11','2018-06-26 01:10:13'),(26,8,0,'Penalty Removal FAQs','2018-05-21','<p>Here are what you need to know in filing a dispute:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>How do I file a dispute?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you are marked as absent due to an AC or MyPage issue, contact Technical Support for dispute validation via <a href=\"http://phsupport.51talk.com/\">http://phsupport.51talk.com/</a></li>\r\n<li>Other absence should be filed to our Fees team by submitting a ticket via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li><strong>How will I know the result of the Tech Dispute Validation?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tech Dispute Validation will be sent via email within 24hours upon filing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li><strong>When will the penalty reversal reflect on my Lesson Fee Summary?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the Tech Dispute Validation results states that the penalty will be reversed within the current cut-off, it will reflect on your Lesson Fee Summary before the current cut-off ends.</li>\r\n<li>If the Tech Dispute Validation results states that the penalty is for supplementation on the next cutoff, the penalty will be supplemented and reflected on your Lesson Fee Summary before the next cut-off ends.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>** Take note that after tech validation, it will still undergo approval process. For follow ups on your penalty reversal/supplementation, you may submit a ticket via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n<li><strong>What will happen to my penalty if there is an AC or MyPage outage?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If there is a system known issue (as posted on PH Support portal home page), your absence and/or penalty on the affected lesson will be reviewed for reversal. Once approved, it will automatically reflect on your Lesson Fee Summary.</li>\r\n<li>All system issues will NOT require tech validation, for concerns/follow-up, you may submit a ticket to our fees team via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li><strong>Why is my dispute invalid?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All lessons filed under Dispute Validation undergo thorough checking. The result is determined by checking our system on any error or issues occurred within the lesson time affected.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>** Take note that all lessons are recorded on the system which allows your dispute validation team to further check on the main issue.</em></p>','2018-05-21 02:34:10','2018-05-29 23:32:06'),(27,8,0,'Penalty Removal: Steps on how to file','2018-05-23','<p>Issues that needs tech dispute validation</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Blank courselist &ndash; <a href=\"/descknow/1/1/25\"><em>click here for troubleshooting</em></a></li>\r\n<li>Lesson Material not loading &ndash; <a href=\"/descknow/1/1/25\"><em>click here for troubleshooting</em></a></li>\r\n<li>Audio/Video issues &ndash; <a href=\"/descknow/1/1/1\"><em>click here for troubleshooting</em></a></li>\r\n<li>Unfilled lesson memo absence due to AC/MyPage issue<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Filing a dispute validation:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to 51Talk support portal via <a href=\"http://phsupport.51talk.com/\">http://phsupport.51talk.com/</a></li>\r\n<li>Click tech support bubble<br /><img src=\"/photos/9/TechBubble.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"301\" height=\"117\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on the specific issue for the troubleshooting steps on the issue you encountered.<br />- Make sure that you conduct the troubleshooting steps to avoid any future penalties.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n<li>Submit a ticket to tech support validation team</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/submit ticket.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"39\" /></li>\r\n<li>Make sure to include the following details<br />a. Lesson Date and Time<br />b. AC Version<br />c. Issue encountered<br />d. Screenshot of the error</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li>Wait for the result within 24 hours after filing.</li>\r\n<li>Result will be sent via email.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**Other absence penalty should be file to our Fees team by submitting a ticket via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2018-05-22 23:30:41','2018-05-22 23:36:40'),(28,1,1,'All You Need to Know about AC 2.14.0.55','2018-06-19','<p><strong>All you need to know on AC 2.14.0.55 Windows platform</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Personalized Feature</li>\r\n<li>Enlarged Video Format</li>\r\n<li>Automatic AC error detection</li>\r\n<li>Automatic CPU and Ram usage detection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Personalized Feature</strong></p>\r\n<p>A New feature of AC that enhance your video AC experienced to be more fun and creative by adding Video background on Both Student Teacher with lots of Face mask and Stickers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to activate:</p>\r\n<p>Click on the Personalized button located besides the star sending feature&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/personalized.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"381\" height=\"36\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lots of Fun feature to choose from all you have to do is drag and drop the selected stickers or Face Mask to your video screen and student</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/stickers.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"275\" height=\"113\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/stickers and mask.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"331\" height=\"208\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>FAQ on Personalized feature</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: How can I remove the sticker that I placed on Video Screen and student?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Click on the Broom Icon located on your video screen to remove the stickers or any features added.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Can my student add their own or removed the personalized fun features?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Teacher are the ones that can activate or deactivate the feature.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Is the Personalized Feature only available on kid&rsquo;s lesson?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Yes</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Enlarged Video Format</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Simply enlarged your video screen to better be seen by students</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s How to activate:</p>\r\n<p>Click on the &ldquo;enlarged video button&rdquo; located below your video screen</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/enlarge icon.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"194\" height=\"162\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/enlarge.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"261\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>FAQ on Enlarged Video format</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: How am I Going to revert back the enlarge video screen?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Click on the &ldquo;Restore&rdquo; button and it will revert back to its original state</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Do Student have this feature?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: It is only applicable on the teacher side</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Automatic AC detection is the new AC intellisense</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AC can now detect the error automatic and will notify the user CPU / RAM usage / Network / Devices and provide a possible fix.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/auto ac.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"658\" height=\"325\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The user will be notified if the CPU and Ram usage are on critical level which is cause by to many windows applications opened.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/cpu ram detect.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"721\" height=\"346\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>FAQ Functionality </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: I notice that the Lesson timer doesn&rsquo;t turn red as an indicator that lesson is near end</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Developer had been informed and it&rsquo;s under development</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Praisal sound is not visible anymore</p>\r\n<p>Answer: It has been removed as part of AC optimization</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Questions: &nbsp;I already installed the AC 2.14.0.55 and I cannot find the personalized feature on any of my kid&rsquo;s lesson.</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Personalized is currently activated on teacher under HBT-FT</p>','2018-06-12 21:51:34','2018-06-26 00:53:34'),(29,8,0,'How to file a penalty dispute ticket','2018-06-19','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please prepare the following:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Lesson Date and time affected</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb